            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="760" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d760">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/10–2445</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Director of the Office of Near Eastern and
                        African Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-24">October 24,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Palestine:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>We have just had word from the British Embassy that Mr. Bevin has decided to
                    postpone the statementon Palestine which he had expected to make in the House of
                    Commons tomorrow. The Embassy has no information concerning the length of
                    postponement but is telegraphing to London immediately the text of the
                    communication which Lord Halifax received from you this morning on the
                    subject.</p>
                <p>[Here follows section concerning the Turkish Straits, printed on <ref target="#pg_1258">page 1258</ref>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Loy</hi> W. <hi rend="smallcaps">Henderson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
